entries.femaleVariant: You look young for a ripperdoc.

entries.maleVariant: I'm lookin' for some new chrome.

entries.femaleVariant: Of course. Get comfortable and we'll get to it.
Depends. Not if your experience doesn't match your years.
I worked ten years in an R&D lab at Moore Technologies. I hope that eases your nerves.
Mind if I ask why you left? Got a feelin' Moore Tech doesn't skimp out on its engineers.
entries.maleVariant: Mind if I ask why you left? I got a feelin' Moore Tech doesn't skimp out on its engineers.

entries.femaleVariant: Sure, the pay was good. But I couldn't sleep.
Moore, as you might know, specializes in deep-tissue integration. Titanium skulls, spine replacements...
It's difficult work. It takes time before a new implant becomes viable, its implementation repeatable. Time... and lives.
